To run a web server, pick one of

	./run-backend <--perl|--ruby>

The perl backend is brought to you by lighttpd and perl, the ruby backend is a rails application.


DEPENDENCIES
------------

./run-backend --perl

This requires lighttpd to be installed, along with the libwww-perl, HTTP-Message, Crypt-OpenSSL-RSA, Crypt-OpenSSL-Random perl libraries. Note than the names may be different on different distributions (yay) these are for Gentoo.


./run-backend --ruby

This requires the ruby application rails.

